\\\\n    --allowedTools \\\"Bash(mise run *),Bash(gh *),Bash(git *),Read,Write,Edit,Glob,Grep\\\"\\n  You are triaging E2E test failures from CI run ${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}.\\n  Follow the /e2e-triage skill instructions in .claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md.\\n  You are in CI mode (WORKFLOW_RUN_ID is set). Use the CI mode steps.\\n  Artifact directory: ${ARTIFACT_DIR}\\n  CI run URL: ${WORKFLOW_RUN_URL}\\n  Re-run failing tests using the e2e-isolated.yml workflow via gh workflow run.\\n  Do NOT ask questions — act autonomously.\\n  For flaky fixes: create a PR.\\n  For real bugs: create or comment on GitHub issues.\\n  Print a summary table at the end.\\n  PROMPT\\n```\\n\\nThis pipes the prompt via stdin, which `claude -p` reads when no positional prompt is given. The heredoc also avoids quoting issues with the multi-line string.\\n\\n## Verification\\n```bash\\ngit push\\ngh workflow run e2e-triage.yml --ref alisha/e2e-triage -f run_id=22772950740\\n```\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-devenv-cli/a1b934a8-baa4-40e5-927d-8b78fbb38d5a.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"2666085f-ddcf-4dc9-a9d9-5c2f4c86c46d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:26:29.411Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: `claude -p` prompt not received due to variadic `--allowedTools` flag\\n\\n## Context\\nThe \\\"Run triage\\\" step in the e2e-triage workflow fails with:\\n```\\nError: Input must be provided either through stdin or as a prompt argument when using --print\\n```\\n\\n**Root cause:** The `--allowedTools` flag accepts variadic arguments (`<tools...>`). When the prompt string follows it as a positional argument, the CLI parser consumes the prompt as another tool name instead of recognizing it as the positional `prompt` argument. So Claude CLI sees no prompt.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n**File: `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`** (lines 81-95